4.3.1 findings in the Czech Republic
EUROCANET can be a significant source of information to identify high-risk Taxpayers in the member state of acquisition.
In the CZ, the early warning information obtained from EUROCANET is reviewed by the competent FA with the acquirers.
Since the first quarter of 2008, CZ has included in the EUROCANET System information on turnover and taxable suppliers considered to be risky.
Nine Czech taxpayers were selected for the audit,
entered into the EUROCANET by the tax administrations of other member states, either as suppliers or purchasers.
