5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two SAIs has proven successful.
Thus, the necessary insights can be gained in both countries, applied systems: This concerns in particular: • intra-community transactions, • risk management at the VAT, in particular with regard to the selection of high-risk transactions • recovery of VAT receivables; and • VAT audit of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and in the systems described above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to stimulate a discussion among interested parties on the audit approaches and anti-fraud strategies that can be used. This applies, for example, to the relationship within and between member states and the EU Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained are intended to encourage the joint examination of the administration of VAT.
